{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"queryExists"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO19CancellableProtocolP","text":"CancellableProtocol"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that in many cases it is "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and then execute something based on the outcome of that, because the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file might have been created or removed in between the operations. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"general approach to handling that is to not check, but just do the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation and handle the errors as they come."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As an example of race-free checking, take the case of reading a file,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and if it doesn’t exist, creating it. There are two racy versions: read"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it, and on error create it; and: check if it exists, if not create it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These can both result in two processes creating the file (with perhaps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a partially written file as the result). The correct approach is to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always try to create the file with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_create()"},{"type":"text","text":" which will either"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atomically create the file or fail with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exists"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, in many cases an existence check is useful in a user interface,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for instance to make a menu item sensitive\/insensitive, so that you don’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have to fool users that something is possible and then just show an error"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dialog. If you do this, you should make sure to also handle the errors"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that can happen due to races when you execute the operation."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/fileprotocol\/queryexists(cancellable:)-7ri1g"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileProtocol\/queryExists(cancellable:)-7ri1g","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Utility function to check if a particular file exists. This is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implemented using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_query_info()"},{"type":"text","text":" and as such does blocking I\/O."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"queryExists(cancellable:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"queryExists"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO12FileProtocolPAAE11queryExists11cancellableSbqd__Sg_tAA011CancellableC0Rd__lF","extendedModule":"GIO","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileProtocol"]]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileProtocol/queryExists(cancellable:)-7ri1g":{"role":"symbol","title":"queryExists(cancellable:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"queryExists"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableT"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Utility function to check if a particular file exists. This is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implemented using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_query_info()"},{"type":"text","text":" and as such does blocking I\/O."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileProtocol\/queryExists(cancellable:)-7ri1g","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileprotocol\/queryexists(cancellable:)-7ri1g"},"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use":{"title":"racy to first check for file existence","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"racy to first check for file existence"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use","url":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"role":"collection","title":"GIO","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"FileProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":" is a high level abstraction for manipulating files on a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"virtual file system. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":"s are lightweight, immutable objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that do no I\/O upon creation. It is necessary to understand that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":" objects do not represent files, merely an identifier for a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file. All file content I\/O is implemented as streaming operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(see [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStream"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStream"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileProtocol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileProtocol"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileprotocol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/OutputStream":{"role":"symbol","title":"OutputStream","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OutputStream"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOutputStream"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class for implementing streaming output."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStream","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OutputStream"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/outputstream"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"CancellableProtocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableProtocol"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InputStream":{"role":"symbol","title":"InputStream","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"InputStream"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputStream"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class for implementing streaming input."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStream","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"InputStream"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/inputstream"}}}